                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>New York</placeName>
                                        <date>Nov 16 1850</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Editor of the Occident</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">In your<lb/> esteemed Paper of <date>Nov.</date>
                                        in an article<lb/> entitled “Letters on Christianity, No 4.
                                        By<lb/> a Jewish layman” Pg 308. The following<lb/> remark
                                        “Not because I fear the effects<lb/> of their writings <hi
                                                  rend="underline">but because the columns
                                                  of</hi><lb/><hi rend="underline"> their religious
                                                  papers are closed to us</hi>”<lb/> I wish to say
                                        to the “<hi rend="underline">Layman</hi>” that I was <lb/>
                                        not before aware of this fact. The “Jewish<lb/> Layman” is
                                        deeply interested in Judaism<lb/> and would sustain it, and
                                        no doubt<lb/> would extend its principles over the world</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">He thinks that fair discussion would<lb/> turn the
                                        scale in favor of Judaism<lb/> If I am wrong in my
                                                  <sic>christian</sic> faith<lb/> I am a lost man.
                                        If Judaism is<lb/> the true way of salvation, upon pain<lb/>
                                        of Endless Perdition I am bound to listen<lb/> to its
                                        teachings, and open my mind<lb/> to conviction of its
                                        truths, and when con<lb/>vinced to embrace it at all worldly
                                                  har<add>?</add>s</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Hence if the “Jewish Laymen” is disposed he<lb/>
                                        is welcome to occupy two or three pages of<lb/> the “Jewish
                                        Chronicle” with sound—kind—and</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>fair discussion every month for the benefit<lb/> of between 2000
                                        &amp; 3000 <sic>christian</sic> readers<lb/> of both
                                        ministers and Layman. Provided<lb/> he can be answered
                                        through your columns<lb/> in articles of Equal length,
                                                  <sic>cander</sic>, kindness<lb/> &amp; fairness. I
                                        mean not this for a challenge<lb/> but in order that the
                                        comparative merits<lb/> of Judaism and Christianity may be
                                        fairly<lb/> placed before the Jewish and Christian
                                        com-<lb/>munities with the highest esteem for<lb/> the
                                        people of <placeName>Israel</placeName> and desire &amp; do
                                        them<lb/> Eternal good. I remain</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Your humble servant</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">E B McGreger</persName>
                                        Editor of</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Jewish Chronicle</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Office Corner of Spruce &amp; Nassau
                                                  St</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <placeName>New York</placeName>
                              </p>
